    <note>Huang(2) Ziyou [863] His fifth generation ancestor, Yuanji(2) [18920], and Huang(2) Xin's [845] (qv.) grandfather served in the administration of the Southern Tang kingdom. Ziyou's great grandfather, Xiaoxian [3415], moved to Huaining, Yuanqiu xian from Jianning, Pucheng xian. Ziyou was Haoqian's [844] grandson. Ziyou moved to Mingzhou, Fenghua xian. He entered civil service on the basis of his uncle Shi's [854] yin. Fujian TZ, 150.39a has him listed as a Pucheng resident who entered on the basis of his grandfather Haoqian's yin. I follow Zhou Bida for address and Fujian TZ for entry. His grandson-in-law, Wu(3) Duo [10085] was Wu(3) Cheng's [10084] grandfather [a CHECK of Cheng's funerary inscription should resolve the issue] and his grandaughter, daughter of Renjian [12933], was betrothed to a Chen Jing, who has the same mingzi as id # [14390],  but Chen Jing(11) [18929] makes better chronological sense. Zhou Bida, WJ, 33.15b-19b; XNYL, 62.1b, 90.3a; Yan Siming, 4.29b. CBD, 4, 2883.</note>
